  "text": "We actually need the result of theorem 1.1 to establish this more basic relation. Indeed, other classical methods fail. For instance, since algebras over a cofibrant prop do not form a model category in general, their homotopy category is difficult to handle directly and we cannot use the machinery of Quillen equivalences. We combine simplicial localization techniques with the properties of ∞-categories, and elaborate on methods introduced in [CITATION_1] about the invariance of classification spaces in the propic setting.",
